I have to say that after a lot of hassle and being let down, Next have finally delivered our sofa and provided us with a full refund, so thank you for that we feel we have been treated fairly at last and thank you to Lisa in complaints

Next has provided terrible service to myself. I ordered 2 sets of new bedroom drawers on the 27th of September- they didn’t arrive until the 15th of October but when they arrived they sent 4 if the same box so I could not make a set of drawers! I had dismantled and my old drawers were away and all my clothes were in boxes! Then to be told they could not send the correct ones out until the 21st so I lived out of boxes for 6 days with 2 babies at 1 and 1 1/2 in the house. I have had 4 boxes in the hall very unsafe! Next then charged me for another 2 sets of drawers so I have been charged for 4 sets! Was told that someone would pick the wrong ones up on Monday 23rd October! Nothing no pick up! I have now been on the phone to next for 27 minutes and been redirected twice as when I’ve been directed to an area it’s been the wrong one, despite me telling them what I was calling for! The pre recorded voice told me they would be with me in 60 seconds that’s been 21 minutes! I’m so disappointed with Next this issue needs to be resolved by this weekend 4 big boxes in my hall is not acceptable! I have had to arrange for someone to be in my house to wait for these to be delivered twice now and this is the 3rd phone call to next and these calls have been very long calls!!

I am heartily sick and tired of the service we are receiving from Next. 23rd July we ordered a sofa , it came 6 weeks later and the delivery people couldn't get it through the door despite not trying very hard, so a new date was made, 2 days before it came we received a call to say they had LOST the sofa, so 6 weeks goes by and another sofa is made, the delivery men this time got it through the door without any problem but it was the wrong sofa, well half of it was. So we waited for another date and yesterday after being promised we were VIP customers and it would be there and my partner taking the day off work we were sent a text to expect it between 7.30 and 18.00, I called at 11.00 to ask what time slot we had and were told sorry (about 1,00000 times now) the system isn't working properly and you wont get your sofa today. I am still waiting for a call . This is disgusting, we have paid over a thousand pounds and still haven't got our sofa.
Hi that sounds like something that happened to my daughter in St Louis!!

Phoned up Thurs someone should have rung back didn't spent 20 mins on the phone this morning still no joy. Still no tables. Seems to be a common problem. Avoid

So Next phoned me on Friday. My sofa delivery date is slowly moving forward. They will deliver a loan sofa on Monday (today) the same as mine only smaller. I don’t really want it but they’re insistent and want to rectify the situation. I’m given an all day delivery slot, 07.30 - 18.00. Don’t worry though, a two hour time slot will be given closer to the time. A two hour time slot was not given. ‘It got delivered at 6 o’clock after she’s waited in all day’ I hear you think. No my friends, it didn’t get delivered at all!!!! Someone is going to be shouted at. My patience has run out.

I have had to result in emailing the complaints department after no help from contacting next home team by phone . Pls be very aware that this company steal from you if you order online. I am totally disgusted at the level of incompetence shown by Next since I placed the order on 28th July 2017. I purchased a sofa, vase, rug and picture frame. They took 3 separate payments from my account. My order was 958 The took 958 then 807 then 10 leaving me 100 overdrawn on my son's birthday. When  I complained they told me it would take 10 days to return my money even after I explained I have bills to pay and children to feed. The money was eventually returned after 12 hours on the phone to various customer advisors. It actually took days. I then received the vase and picture frame smashed to pieces. They agreed to replace. I then received 2 picture frames no vase but they charged me 3 times for both items taking a further 32 from my account then another 30. No explanation they then delivered my sofa in the wrong colour this was after an entire morning and early afternoon chasing them for a delivery time. They emailed  4 different delivery times then emailed saying actually are not going to deliver you. Only for me to find them sat at the end of my road with my sofa on the delivery van. Wrong colour sofa. There are now none available in the colour I wanted but I sold my other furniture so my children and I now have nothing to sit on for 12 weeks. I order a new sofa from somewhere else on the promise that I will pay the £ 1,000 deposit this week as NEXT promised to collect  the sofas yesterday. I explained that I had to work, they stated it was fine for my 15 year old son to see them in to collect. They turned up late and refused to take the sofa. Meaning they still hold £958 of my money. I called yesterday to speak to Zoreen who dealt with my original complaint or Ian the manager who agreed the collection. Neither of them returned my call. The frustration caused by being on the phone to this Company ended with me dropping my phone in the sink losing me another £ 450 and hundreds of photos of my children. Despite me calling 6 times to give NEXT a different number to call me back on they continue to call my old phone?? I have never dealt with such a bunch of morons in my life. Bar Arrow xl
